# Banking api

A restful api to manage users, account, and also authentication
Built with node js(express), postgres(prisma orm) and typescript


## Features

- User authentication (JWT)
- Account management
- Secure password hashing
- Secure money transfer with prisma transactions

## Tech Stack

- Node.js
- Express
- TypeScript
- Prisma ORM
- PostgreSQL
- Jest & Supertest (testing)
- ioredis for cache
- resend from email
- redis and express-rate-limit for rate limiting


## Installation

1. Clone the repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/your-api.git
cd your-api

2. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install

3. Database configuration

DATABASE_URL=your_database_url
JWT_SECRET=your_secret

4. Run the migration

```bash
npx prisma migrate dev
npx prisma generate



---

# 📡 5. API Endpoints

```md
## API Endpoints

### Auth

POST /banking/register  
POST /banking/login  
POST /banking/logout
POST /banking/refresh
POST /banking/forgot-password
POST /banking/reset-password/:token

### Users

GET /banking/users
GET /banking/users/:id
GET /banking/users/:userId
DELETE /banking/:userId
PATCH /banking/:userId  

### Account

GET /account  
POST /transfer
GET /transfer
GET /transfer/:id



## Example: Login

### Request

POST /banking/login

```json
{
  "email": "test@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Response
{
  "success": true 
  "message": "Login successful",
  "data": access_token
}

###The access token will be saved in cookie

## Example: Register

### Request

POST /banking/register

```json
{
  "name": "test"
  "email": "test@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Response
{
  "success": true 
  "message": "Registration successful, email verification ahs been sant to you email",
  "data": user_data
}


## Environment Variables

- DATABASE_URL
- JWT_SECRET
- PORT
- resend_api_key
- resend_from
- accessTokenSecret
- refreshTokenSecret
- base_url